    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-29T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="660"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-29T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 29, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>333. Your 1004, July 23, 1 p.m. The Department thoroughly appreciates the
                    desirability of extending aid to Saudi Arabia and the question is receiving
                    every attention: Legal difficulties apparently make impossible an unsecured
                    loan, from this Government to that of King Ibn Saud, but the Reconstruction
                    Finance Corporation is considering means whereby credit may be extended against
                    collateral <pb facs="0650" n="642" xml:id="pg_642"/> in the form of future
                    deliveries of petroleum products. A decision is expected very shortly.</p>
                <p>In your discretion you may informally advise the Saudi Arabian Legation that its
                    request is receiving the closest attention of this Government and that a reply
                    will be made at the earliest possible moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
